Run the below commands to prepare the environment:

yum install pip
pip install PyYAML
pip install boto3
pip install paramiko

In the assignment.yaml file provide your details for the following variables
key_pair - the name of the key pair that you have created. FOllow the instructions in the https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ec2-key-pairs.html to create a keypair.
aws_access_key_id - give your access key ID. Follow the instructions in the https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/aws-sec-cred-types.html to get your ID.
aws_secret_access_key - Give your secret access key. Follow the instructions in the https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/aws-sec-cred-types.html to get they key.
path_pem - when you create a key pair it will be downloaded in your PC by the browser. Provide the path of the .pem file here.
and run the script test.py.
The command to run the test.py is "python test.py"

To ssh into the instance that is been created please execute the below command.
ssh -i /tmp/assignment.pem user1@yourIP

you can get the IP in AWS EC2 after the python code is executed.

